data.item: Did you know that music can make you smarter? Multiple studies prove how listening to music increases cognitive performance - University of Kansas Medical Centre found
If you love listening to music while you workout, good news! Music has been scientifically proven to make you
workout harder! Studies show that those who workout with music workout harder and their perceived exertion is lower.

Not only does music help you workout harder but also speeds up recovery. Researchers found that music speeds up post exercise recovery and that music tastes did not affect the recovery rate. Another study found that listening to music improves the recovery of stroke patients.
Can listening to music turn you into superhuman? Probably not, but researchers from University of Utah's Pain Research Center found that listening to music helped people to feel less pain.
Fancy seeing your favourite artist live? Well now you have an excuse. Research has shown that live music is more effective than taped music at reducing anxiety and improving mood.

Need to relax? Just listen to some music! Many studies have shown that music can significantly reduce stress and anxiety levels. According to one study, listening to music that you enjoy on a daily basis can significantly lower your levels of stress, and is more effective at lowering anxiety than the sedative Midazolam. Another study found that music's effect on anxiety levels is similar to that of getting a massage!!
Music can actually be good for your heart. Researchers have discovered that listening to joyful music can help promote a healthy heart.
